	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p>All that is good forever to my brother&#45;<lb/> in&#45;law <persName>Itzik</persName> In the hope that<lb/> these lines find you in good health. I<lb/> write this to let you know that&#44; God be<lb/> thanked&#44; we are well... Moreover&#44; I want<lb/> to let you know that we received your<lb/> first letter&#44; in which you wished both of us<lb/> good luck&#44; which you wrote on the <date>second of<lb/> Heshvan</date> and which reached us a few days<lb/> ago. Perhaps the ship which carried the letter<lb/> came under the embargo and <placeName>England</placeName> held<lb/> the ship back. As soon as transportation<lb/> was begun again&#44; the Postmaster wrote to<lb/> me that a letter to my address was being<lb/> held and that as soon as I would send<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> he would send the letter to me.</p>
				<p rend="Translator&#39;s note&#58;"><persName>Leeser</persName> evidently sent money to his<lb/> brother&#45;in&#45;law&#44; but for what purpose&#44; it<lb/> is not clear.&#41;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You write that you hope I am a good<lb/> Jew. Don&#39;t doubt it You may be sure I</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>come of a good family&#44; and I also<lb/> am a Schochet. To our uncle<lb/> <persName>Zalman</persName> we have already written...</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your brother&#45;in&#45;law who calls<lb/> himself <persName role="author">Zvi ben Jacob Katz</persName>.</p>
				<p>Addressed to <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
		</body>
